title: Getting started
text: domestic point source (DPS) functions designed work raw entity data provided partners. core function anlz_dps_facility() requires vector file paths input, path points file monthly parameter concentration (mg/L) flow data (million gallons per day). data also describe whether observations end pipe (direct inflow bay) reuse (applied land), defined outfall Ids typically noted D-001, D-002, etc. R-001, R-002, etc, respectively. estimated concentration times flow, whereas reuse includes attenuation factor land application depending location. file names must follow specific convention, metadata entity found facilities() data object using information file name. convenience, four example files included package. files represent actual entities facilities, data randomized. paths files used input function. Non-trivial data pre-processing quality control needed file included package correct format. output returned tons per month TN, TP, TSS, BOD million cubic meters per month flow (hy). anlz_dps() function uses anlz_dps_facility() summarize DPS results location facility (combines outfall data), entity (combines facility data), bay segment (combines entity data), (combines bay segment data). results can also temporally summarized monthly annual totals. location summary defined summ argument temporal summary defined summtime argument. fls argument used anlz_dps_facility() also used anlz_dps(). output tons per month TN, TP, TSS, BOD million cubic meters per month flow (hy) summtime = 'month' tons per year TN, TP, TSS, BOD million cubic meters per year flow (hy) summtime = 'year'.

title: Getting started
text: Material losses (ML) estimates nutrient loads bay primarily fertilizer shipping activities ports. Historically, loadings material losses much higher present. entities report material losses, typically total year total nitrogen. material losses tons/yr estimated tons shipped using agreed upon loss rate. Values reported example files represent estimated loss total tons N shipped year multiplied 0.0023 divided 2000. total N shipped facility year can obtained using simple back-calculation (multiply 2000, divide 0.0023). core function anlz_ml_facility() requires vector file paths input, file one row per year per facility, row shows total tons per year total nitrogen loss. file names must follow specific convention, metadata entity found facilities() data object using information file name. convenience, four example files included package. files represent actual entities facilities, data randomized. paths files used input function. output nearly identical input data since load calculations used, except results shown monthly load annual loss divided 12. Additional empty columns (e.g., TP load, TSS load, etc.) also returned consistency reporting loading sources. anlz_ml() function uses anlz_ml_facility() summarize IPS results location facility, entity (combines facility data), bay segment (combines entity data), (combines bay segment data). results can also temporally summarized monthly annual totals. location summary defined summ argument temporal summary defined summtime argument. fls argument used anlz_ml_facility() also used anlz_ml(). output tons per month TN summtime = 'month' tons per year TN summtime = 'year'. Columns TP, TSS, BOD, hydrologic load also returned zero load consistency point source load calculation functions. Material loss loads often combined IPS loads reporting.

title: Getting started
text: Loading atmospheric deposition (AD) bay segments Tampa Bay watershed calculated using rainfall data weather stations watershed atmospheric concentration data Verna Wellfield site. Rainfall data must obtained using util_ad_getrain() function calculating loads. convenience, daily rainfall data 2017 2023 sites watershed included package ad_rain object. Verna Wellfield data must also obtained https://nadp.slh.wisc.edu/sites/ntn-FL41/ monthly observations. file also included package can found using system.file() follows: load calculation, Verna data converted total nitrogen total phosphorus ammonium nitrate concentration data using util_ad_prepverna() function. Total nitrogen phosphorus concentrations estimated ammonium nitrate concentrations (mg/L) using following relationships: TN=NH4+*0.78+NO3−*0.23 TN = NH_4^+ * 0.78 + NO_3^- * 0.23 TP=0.01262*TN+0.00110 TP = 0.01262 * TN + 0.00110 first equation corrects % ions ammonium nitrate N, second regression relationship TBADS TN TP, applied Verna. AD loads estimated using anlz_ad() function, total hydrologic load bay segment calculated rain data total nitrogen phosphorus load calculated multiplying hydrologic load atmospheric deposition concentrations Verna data. Total hydrologic load bay segment calculated using daily estimates rainfall NWIS NCDC sites watershed. done weighted mean rainfall measured sites relative grid locations bay segment. weights based distance grid cells closest site inverse distance squared. Total hydrologic load sub-watershed estimated converting inches/month m3/month using area bay segment. distance data bay segment areas contained file included package. total nitrogen phosphorus loads estimated bay segment multiplying total hydrologic load total nitrogen phosphorus concentrations Verna data. loading calculations also include wet/dry deposition conversion factor account differences loading rainy dry seasons. Using anlz_ad() estimate AD load done follows, ad_rain rain data vernafl path Verna Wellfield data. Results can summarized segment, baywide, monthly, annually using summ summtime arguments. default, loads returned monthly segment. Note Boca Ciega Bay Boca Ciega Bay South results returned separately. Boca Ciega Bay South used estimating total bay loads.

code: fls <- list.files(system.file('extdata/', package = 'tbeploads'),   pattern = 'ps_ind_', full.names = TRUE)  ipsbyfac <- anlz_ips_facility(fls)  # add bay segment and source, there should only be loads to hills, middle, and lower tampa bay ipsld <- ipsbyfac  |>   dplyr::arrange(coastco) |>   dplyr::left_join(dbasing, by = "coastco") |>   dplyr::mutate(     segment = dplyr::case_when(       bayseg == 1 ~ "Old Tampa Bay",       bayseg == 2 ~ "Hillsborough Bay",       bayseg == 3 ~ "Middle Tampa Bay",       bayseg == 4 ~ "Lower Tampa Bay",       TRUE ~ NA_character_     ),     source = 'IPS'   ) |>   dplyr::select(-basin, -hectare, -coastco, -name, -bayseg)  util_ps_summ(ipsld, summ = 'entity', summtime = 'year') #> # A tibble: 5 × 9 #>    Year source entity         segment  tn_load tp_load tss_load bod_load hy_load #>   <int> <chr>  <chr>          <chr>      <dbl>   <dbl>    <dbl>    <dbl>   <dbl> #> 1  2020 IPS    Busch Gardens  Hillsbo…  0.437   0.0858   6.11       11.7  1.11   #> 2  2021 IPS    Coronet        Hillsbo…  0.0305  0.0515   0.0662      0    0.0184 #> 3  2017 IPS    Lowry Park Zoo Hillsbo…  0.215   0.0612   0           0    0.188  #> 4  2018 IPS    Lowry Park Zoo Hillsbo…  0.168   0.0456   0           0    0.140  #> 5  2019 IPS    Lowry Park Zoo Hillsbo…  0.0950  0.0226   0           0    0.0763
